L067:ops:!c:opus46-desktop-aggdb-frontend-deploy-001
Git not in system PATH on Antiquarian breaks Git LFS, Chrome extension, MCP shell git operations
Git installed at C:\Program Files\Git\bin\git.exe but not in PATH. Full-path git commands work for log/branch/add but LFS filter subprocess fails on commit/status because LFS invokes bare 'git'. Fix: add Git dirs to system PATH (admin required). Likely root cause of Chrome extension blocking same day.

L068:ops:c:opus46-desktop-aggdb-frontend-deploy-001
MCP Shell on Antiquarian: use bat files with set GIT= variable for git commands
cmd.exe set PATH= does not reliably persist in MCP-spawned shells. Workaround: write .bat files using set GIT="full\path" and %GIT% variable for all git commands. Git Bash is another option but harder to invoke from MCP. Start-Process pwsh -File works for non-git PowerShell scripts.

